    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-27T19:00:00-05:00" n="1084"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1084">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3513/6–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-28T09:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 28, 1949—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 29—1:17 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192. Clerk Chao has not gone home last 2 months due fear difficulties with Soviet
                    and CCP police (Contel 40, March 3, repeated 62<note n="33" xml:id="d1084fn33"
                        >Not printed.</note>). Rarely leaves Consulate premises. Now learned for
                    first time his 19-year-old son arrested 3 weeks ago and just released from
                    prison. Son was asked give information father’s work at Consulate; warned that
                    unless he told all he knew regarding father’s spying activities he would suffer
                    serious consequences.</p>
                <p>As result pressure used on him in prison, son’s mind affected.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 141, repeated Department, Canton 182, Shanghai 159, Moscow 108.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
